Mon May 27 20:58:17 1996    <kehr@eliade.hrz.th-darmstadt.de>

	* Some weeks of hard work are finished. The markup is completely
	  finished. The cross-references are fully implemented. The letter
	  groups, too. The sort- and merge-rules for keywords seem to
	  word. It's great! The indexstyle is nearly complete. Still
	  missing is a good startup-script and the TeX-frontend
	  (Joachim promised to make it for me). The print-key is still not
	  implemented. It is very simple but I most think about the
	  correct policy. Still missing is the building of
	  location-reference trees. Maybe it is comparable to the
	  indexentry trees, we'll see.

	  The complete markup-scheme suits me fine. I like the way to
	  describe how the index should look like. With the debugging mode
	  turned on, everybody sees exactly what markup-entities are
	  called and one can successively replace them with your own
	  markup-tags. Maybe this was one of my best ideas. Now users can
	  master the markup in an autodidactic and interactive way. More
	  experience and suggests are welcome.

