Wed Mar 27 21:29:27 1996  Roger Kehr  <kehr@spock>

	* Long, long ago I wrote my last ChangeLog. I passed one exam some
	  days ago---the next one comes soon....

	  Ok, I spent most of the time with clisp, its compilation and the
	  handling of the foreign function interface. After experimenting
	  with the regexp library from the clisp distibution I decided to
	  move to the newer GNU Rx library. I wrote a regsub function in
	  Lisp (the function was built by the program and evaluated later)
	  I took one more look into the old makeindex3-project and
	  discovered, that it might be better to include some parts of the
	  source (written in C) into my project. The reasons were simple.
	  First these parts were well tested and only minor modifications
	  (that's a lie) were neccessary to get it running under the Rx
	  library. Additionally I wrote a `rxsub' routine (now in C) that
	  implements the desired features im a more efficient way (it's
	  damn fast!). Now I have a bunch of C-modules that are directly
	  reachable from clisp.

